dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim b Rabada 11 (20b 2x4 0x6 35m) SR: 55

dismissalComment.html: stumps go splat, and that is Test wicket No.300 for Kagiso Rabada! Proper hot knife through butter stuff. Begins on a length outside off before curving back in delightfully. Decks back into Mushfiqur off the surface too and he is just too late to cover the line. Breezes through the gap between bat and pad, and leaves the stumps in an absolute mess. South Africa have their fourth, and Bangladesh are reeling!

dismissalComment.html: trapped in front, and given lbw! Maharaj and co hardly even appealed, before the finger was up! But Jaker reviews. Maharaj tossed the ball up, and bowled on a length. UltraEdge shows there is a gap between bat and ball, so there is no inside edge, as he is hit on his left leg after opening his stance up.
